<br>
Hot-Keys are your friends. I think I have about 25 in all. They are one of our best group communication tools and being an Enchanter I think it is one of the most important thing we can do. Sure we spam the group chat and at times we may seem like the dictators of the group, but lets face it the key to success for single group/multi raiding is communication. <br>
<br>
Since mezzing takes up the most part of our mana what better way to conserve it would be by announcing which mobs are mezzed and which mobs need to be attacked next. i.e.  "Mezzing -- A Blizzard Spider ----" and "A Blizzard Spider is next on the Menu".<br>
<br>
Another helpful thing to do as well is assign roots. This not only helps your chanter mez them without getting pummeled to death and having to chain cast stuns so you have a moment to mez it. I just love when Wizards and Shammys and those that can root do so. Problem is I rarely hear them announce it, until after the fact when you are a dead chanter and home point and they say in group.. "Well it was rooted you know"...<br>
<br>
Announcing your slows prior to casting is good too. Slow has to be one of the number 1 taunts I know. Because slows should be done as soon as possible without trying to gain to much aggro there is a very good chance you will get the mob on you. Let the tanks know you are about to get mauled so taunters are focused on taunting and others on rooting. <br>
<br>
Since we each have our own style of mezzing, passing any information on to your group is helpful. Tell them that you want roots or maybe you don't.. I hope this helps some in the importance of communication within a group of people. After all you are going to be spending a few hours with them, why not make it run smoother and enjoyable for all? <p><font color="red">~Mymic Mystique~<BR>
